description: Waystream Holding AB engages in the development and sale of broadband equipment for residential and business users. The company is headquartered in Kista, Stockholm and currently employs 16 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2015-11-12. The firm provides access switches for broadband and enterprise networks, such as software-defined networking (DSN) and fiber-to-the-home (FTTH) networks to Layer Two and Layer Three broadband networks. Its products include Gigabit-t0-the-home (GTTH) routers and switches under the brands ASR, ServiceEngine and MetroStar, among others. In addition, the Company develops iBOS, an operating system used to configure its routers and switches. The firm operates facilities in Kista and is active in around 25 countries.
